    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-14T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-14T09:00:00-05:00" n="204"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d204">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">853B.20/51: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Ponta Delgada, Azores</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ponta Delgada</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-14T13:00:00-01:00"
                            >April 14, 1942—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 2:22 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>119 Referring to the Department’s telegram No. 15, April 7, 11 p.m., General
                    Passos e Sousa, believed to be former Minister of War, arrived yesterday from
                    Lisbon on the destroyer <hi rend="italic">Vouga</hi>, reportedly for the purpose
                    of investigating the conduct of the military commander.</p>
                <p>A military censorship of all mail, incoming, outgoing and local was established
                    yesterday morning.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
